The paper deals with fairness in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses bias in data, which is relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) as well as social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes recommended procedures for dealing with missing data, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
